1. Oni *sile* svoju volju na druge. (They *force* their will onto others.)
2. Vi ne biste smeli da *sila*te decu da jedu. (You shouldn't *force* children to eat.)
3. Njegova *silna* želja da postane glumac ga je dovela u pozorište. (His *strong* desire to become an actor brought him to the theater.)
4. *Silom* je otvorio vrata koja su bila zaglavljena. (He *forced* the door open that was stuck.)
5. Iako je bio bolestan, *silom* se trudio da održi svoju formu. (Although he was sick, he *forcefully* tried to maintain his shape.)
6. Njegova *silovita* reakcija pokazuje koliko mu je stalo do toga. (His *powerful* reaction shows how much he cares about it.)
7. Nažalost, situacija je *izvan sile* ljudi da se promeni. (Unfortunately, the situation is *beyond the control* of people to change.)
8. *Silom prilika*, morao je da ode iz svoje zemlje i započne novi život u inostranstvu. (Due to *circumstances beyond his control*, he had to leave his country and start a new life abroad.)
9. Moramo pronaći *sredinu* između njihovih zahteva i naših mogućnosti. (We need to find a *middle ground* between their demands and our capabilities.)
10. Njihova *silna* želja da uspeju ih je navela da rade naporno i ne odustaju. (Their *strong* desire to succeed has driven them to work hard and not give up.)